  <sec>
    <title>Conclusion</title>
    <p>Allim is an open-source and user-friendly tool, which estimates allele-specific gene expression in F1 crosses. It provides an integrated pipeline for estimating the allele-specific gene expression and allelic imbalance tests. Compared to other available software tools, Allim provides a range of additional features and allows for a wide range of input options.</p>
  </sec>
  <sec>
    <title>Obtaining Allim</title>
    <p>Allim requires Python 2.7.3, R 2.15.0 and other third-party tools and works on all Unix operating system. The source code, user manual and test data sets are available online from <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://code.google.com/p/allim/">http://code.google.com/p/allim/</ext-link>.</p>
  </sec>
